---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../lib/site-config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="about"
  description="ClaudeStack — written by a practitioner shipping production systems with Claude Code, not an influencer summarizing other people's tweets."
>
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="page-meta">manifest / why this exists</div>
        <h1 class="page-title">written by a <span class="accent">practitioner</span>.</h1>

        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            ClaudeStack is a publication, not a content farm. It exists because the gap between
            "I tried Claude for a weekend" tweets and the lived experience of shipping a real
            product with AI coding agents is enormous, and almost nothing public is filling it.
          </p>

          <p>
            Every article here is written from the seat of someone running production code that
            handles real money or real users. Patterns are tested for at least three months
            before they become essays. Numbers are real. Failures are documented because the
            failures are usually more useful than the successes.
          </p>

          <h2>What you'll find here</h2>

          <p>
            Three kinds of writing, deliberately:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Essays</strong> — opinionated arguments about how to build with AI agents. Written when something has clicked and is worth defending.</li>
            <li><strong>Patterns</strong> — reusable techniques. The orchestrator pattern. SPEC-driven development. The audit loop. Things that survived contact with production.</li>
            <li><strong>Guides</strong> — walk-through references for specific tools or workflows. Less argument, more "here's exactly how I do X."</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>What you won't find</h2>

          <ul>
            <li>"10 prompts that will change your life" lists.</li>
            <li>Hot takes on yesterday's announcement.</li>
            <li>Affiliate-laundered tool reviews.</li>
            <li>Anything I haven't actually shipped with.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Who writes this</h2>

          <p>
            One person. {siteConfig.author}. I'm building an algorithmic trading hedge fund as
            the actual day job — Claude Code is the primary instrument I use to ship that code.
            ClaudeStack is the place where the patterns I find useful get written down so they're
            not lost to chat history.
          </p>

          <p>
            If you'd like to argue with anything you read here, the <a href="mailto:hello@claudestack.dev">contact link</a> is real. If you want the new posts in your inbox, the <a href="#newsletter">newsletter</a> is the right place. If you want to support the work, the <a href="/shop">guide</a> is for sale.
          </p>

          <h2>What this site is not trying to be</h2>

          <p>
            Not a community. Not a course platform. Not a SaaS. Not a media business.
            A publication, full stop. Long-lived essays, written carefully, with the
            assumption that someone might read them in three years and the patterns
            should still hold up.
          </p>

          <p>
            That's it. Welcome.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
